title: Solo (2018)
body:
Dir. Ron Howard

Synopsis

How the young Han Solo met Chewie, acquired the Millennium Falcon and began along the path to hero.

What’s To Like

It’s a Star Wars movie with the usual action special effects. Alden Ehrenreich tries hard to be a young version of the cynical Solo with hints of the mannerisms used by Harrison Ford. A superb villain in Dryden Vos, played admirably by Paul Bettany.

Quibbles

So much of the back-story was rushed: how fun it would have been to see Han as an Imperial trooper. Indeed, the main quibble is that it spent so much attention on the elements of the back-story (the Millenium Falcon, Chewie, Calrissian etc.) that it forgot to be exciting and entertaining in its own tale. And did we really have to endure yet another ‘cantina’ scene?

Rating ***

Recommendation

Die-hard Star Wars fans will feel the Force impelling them to see it. For the rest of us, the decision to work on a new trilogy whilst interpolating stand-alone films has resulted in the franchise becoming repetitive and losing pace. Yes, we will go see the stand-alone Bobba Fett movie and also Episode IX. But please, let’s end it there!
